What is domain squatting? Domain squatting is when someone registers a domain name which looks like another domain name. Usually, the term &ldquo;domain squatting&rdquo; is used in a context where malicious intent is implied. For example, someone trying to steal passwords may register the domain name gooogle.

In doing QA-esque things for friends and coworkers, I have noticed that some people do not have a good sense of how to &lsquo;QA&rsquo; something. I compiled a short list of questions below that I ask myself.
Testing Inputs Does the system handle1&hellip;
Different Quantities a little input? a lot? A LOT? nothing? a &lsquo;normal&rsquo; amount? one value that is really short? one value that is really loooonnnnnnggggg? Different Qualities something of a weird type?
